-- Anglo May Settle Chile Mine Dispute This Week, Sunday Times Says
-- B y   P a u l   D o b s o n
-- 2012-08-19T11:37:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-19/anglo-may-settle-chile-mine-dispute-this-week-sunday-times-says.html
Anglo American Plc (AAL)  may reach a deal
this week to settle a dispute with Chile’s state-owned copper
company over the world’s fifth-largest copper mine, the Sunday
Times  reported , without saying where it got the information.  Anglo is considering selling 24.5 percent of the Los
Bronces project at a deep discount to an original, below-market
valuation after a legal dispute, the newspaper said.  Emily Blyth, a spokeswoman for Anglo American in  London ,
declined to comment on the Sunday Times report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Dobson in London at 
